  "text": "The error 'upstream connect error or disconnect/reset before headers. reset reason: overflow' occurs when Envoy's connection pool exhausts circuit breaker thresholds for maximum pending requests or active requests.\n\n**Root Cause - Where 'overflow' String is Defined:**\nThe string 'overflow' is defined in source/common/http/utility.cc:1031 in the resetReasonToString() function, which maps the enum Http::StreamResetReason::Overflow to the literal string 'overflow'.\n\n**Connection Pool Implementation - Where Overflow is Triggered:**\nThe ConnectionPool::PoolFailureReason::Overflow condition is triggered in source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc at two critical points:\n\n1. **Max Pending Requests (lines 282-287):** In ConnPoolImplBase::newStreamImpl(), when no ready clients are available, the connection pool checks if pendingRequests().canCreate() returns false. If the current pending request count has reached the max_pending_requests circuit breaker limit, onPoolFailure() is called with PoolFailureReason::Overflow.\n\n2. **Max Active Requests (lines 175-179):** In ConnPoolImplBase::attachStreamToClient(), when attaching an active stream to a client, the pool checks if requests().canCreate() returns false. If max_requests limit is reached, onPoolFailure() is called with PoolFailureReason::Overflow.\n\nThese circuit breaker limits are enforced via the ResourceManagerImpl class (source/common/upstream/resource_manager_impl.h), which manages three key resource limits:\n- connections: max concurrent connections to upstream\n- pendingRequests: max pending connection attempts\n- requests: max active requests per connection\n\n**Circuit Breaker Configuration (Protobuf):**\nThe configuration is defined in api/envoy/config/cluster/v3/circuit_breaker.proto and its v2 counterpart in the data-plane-api repository (envoy/config/cluster/v3/circuit_breaker.proto and envoy/api/v2/cluster/circuit_breaker.proto). Key fields:\n- max_connections (field 2): Default 1024\n- max_pending_requests (field 3): Default 1024\n- max_requests (field 4): Default 1024\n\n**Call Chain to Error Message:**\n1. Connection pool detects overflow at stream creation (newStreamImpl or attachStreamToClient)\n2. Calls onPoolFailure() with PoolFailureReason::Overflow\n3. Router's UpstreamRequest::onPoolFailure() converts it to Http::StreamResetReason::Overflow\n4. Router::onUpstreamReset() calls Utility::resetReasonToString() which returns 'overflow'\n5. Error is logged as 'reset reason: overflow' in source/common/router/router.cc:1418\n\n**HTTP Connection Pool Hierarchy:**\nThe HTTP connection pool (source/common/http/conn_pool_base.h) extends the base ConnectionPool::ConnPoolImplBase, delegating overflow handling to the parent class while providing HTTP-specific codec client management."
}

